            "answer_text": "2.45 times as far. Let\u2019s assume spitting horizontally. The amount of time it takes to fall to the ground would be t=sqrt(2h/g). Lowering g to 1/6 its original value would give you a difference of sqrt(1/(1/6)) or sqrt(6) = 2.45. You spit will remain in the air 2.45 x longer and hence will be able to go 2.45x farther. ",
